GBrowse syn Tutorial new Further Reading A Note on Whole Genome Alignments The focus of the section of the course is on dealing with alignment or synteny data and using GBrowse_syn. However, how to generate whole genome alignments, identify orthologous regions, etc, are the subject of considerable interest, so some background reading is listed below:
GMOD Components GBrowse syn Facts about &ldquo;GBrowse syn Tutorial new&quot;
Has topic GBrowse syn + Navigation menu Navigation GMOD Home Software Categories / Tags Documentation Overview FAQs HOWTOs Glossary Community GMOD News Training / Outreach Support GMOD Promotion Meetings Calendar Tools Browse properties

GMOD Middleware This is a summary and detailed notes from the Chado Middleware Bake Off held at the January 2007 GMOD Meeting.
Executive Summary Although GMOD uses the Chado schema for its underlying database, each group has developed a separate interface to their databases. This meeting was designed to review the experiences each group has had with its particular solution and to recommend a &ldquo;best practice.&rdquo;
All participants had developed some type of Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) tool.

