Meetings &ldquo;It&rsquo;s tempting to see bioinformatics as a collection of potential problems. Being at a GMOD meeting helps us see bioinformatics as a collection of potential solutions.&rdquo;
Isabelle Phan, SBRI, and past GMOD meeting participant
GMOD has put on several types of meetings, including semi-annual community meetings and specialized hackathons. GMOD content is also presented at Training and Outreach events, run both by GMOD and by other organizations. All these events are listed on the GMOD Calendar.

News/BioMart Ruby API Daz Oakley of the Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute has released a Ruby library/API for BioMart. Daz says &ldquo;It&rsquo;s quite basic for the moment and only does single dataset queries, but it will be quite easy to build upon the base from here.&rdquo;
The source is available from GitHub, and the documentation is at rdoc.info.
The Ruby API is the latest addition to a growing list of third party software that supports BioMart.

