Using the topoview Glyph This glyph is derived from the FlyBase fb_shmiggle Glyph, 2009-2010 Victor Strelets, FlyBase.org
It is maintained by Sheldon McKay &lt;sheldon.mckay@gmail.com&gt;
The TopoView glyph was developed for fast 3D-like demonstration of RNA-seq data consisting of multiple individual subsets. The main purposes were to compact presentation as much as possible (in one reasonably sized track) and to allow easy visual detection of coordinated behavior of the expression profiles of different subsets.

